name: Different - Week 4
description: As we get older, we gravitate toward what's comfortable. This pull from courageous to complacent fights against what God wants to do in us. The abundant life and amazing love Jesus wants us to experience always lie on the other side of faith steps and bold moves.

name: Weekly All Staff - Ken Wilson & Howard Frist
Different - Week 2
description: God is a promise maker and promise keeper. Hear from our lead pastors how God builds our faith individually and corporately when we trust His promises.

name: Different - Week 1
description: We were made to be different. But we won't get there by doing what we've always done. This requires a change from the inside out. We'll have to think different to be different. Only then will we begin to do things differently and live in a way that makes a difference.

name: Christmas At NewSpring 2017
description: Christmas is about three things: the gift, the giver, and the response. Jesus is God’s gift to us, and our response to His arrival shapes more than how we see Christmas. It changes how we live.

name: DYSWIS - Week 3
description: The wise men had everything society says we need: money, education, respect, power. Still, they weren’t satisfied. So they packed their bags and followed a star on the search for something more. Like the wise men, all of us are born with a longing that can only be fulfilled in Jesus.

name: Rally at Passion 2018
description: Join us for Passion 2018! Passion Conference exists to see a generation leverage their lives for what matters most.

name: Vroom: New series starting in KidSpring
description:
The checkered flags are waving, and we’re off to the races. We believe God is going to do incredible things in 2018, and we’re excited to jump into a new series at KidSpring.

During “Vroom,” we will be racing through God’s Word to see what He says about how we can love Him and love others!

name: DYSWIS - Week 2
description: Mary’s cousin Elizabeth understood what it’s like to long for something. Through decades of infertility, Elizabeth probably cried out to God often. We all have our own “God, all I want is ____!” prayers. For Elizabeth and for us, Christmas is a reminder that the thing we’re waiting for isn’t the point. It’s a pointer to the real promise.

name: DYSWIS - Week 3
description: Mary’s cousin Elizabeth understood what it’s like to long for something. Through decades of infertility, Elizabeth probably cried out to God often. We all have our own “God, all I want is ____!” prayers. For Elizabeth and for us, Christmas is a reminder that the thing we’re waiting for isn’t the point. It’s a pointer to the real promise.

name: Kingdom (Fuse) - Week 2
description: The Kingdom is here, it is at hand. What does this mean?

name: DYSWIS - Week 1
description: Does God really care about the little guy? When we're lonely or struggling to get by, it's hard to imagine that God can relate. But the angel's announcement to the shepherds reminds us that God sees all of us. Even when we don't see things the way He does.

name: Learn more about the Overflow Offering

name: Thankful - Week 3
description: Trials fall upon everyone. Even good people who make good decisions. Gratitude isn’t the natural response when hard times come, but it’s in the testing and the trials that faith grows and perseverance develops.

name: ThankFULL - Week 1
description: Thankfulness is more than practicing good manners. Thankfulness has incredible power. It will guard your heart, align your soul, and reveal Jesus in every situation.

name: Spirit - Week 1
description: If you're a Christian, it's the Holy Spirit that lives inside of you and fills you.

name: Slaying Giants - Week 5
description: Anxiety attacks everyone. When we go through difficult or stressful situations, our bodies remember and fear alerts us when danger presents itself again. Anxiety doesn’t mean we’re bad people or that we’re crazy. But it will tear us apart if we don’t face its cause.

name: Slaying Giants - Week 4
description: Ever felt like someone else was living the life you were meant to have? That’s what comparison does. It convinces us that God plus something else  — a spouse, a child, a house, a promotion — will be enough. Don't let comparison stop you from enjoying the life God has for you.

name: Slaying Giants - Week 3
description: "When someone hurts you, do you pretend it never happened or silently plot your revenge? Maybe you hold a grudge ""to teach 'em a lesson.""\n\nBitterness can creep into all of our lives. But instead of punishing our offender, bitterness punishes us. It holds us hostage to the past and destroys relationships in the process. Bitterness doesn't have to hold you back. Slaying the giant of bitterness starts with understanding the power of forgiveness. "

name: North Pole News
description: New series starting in KidSpring on Dec. 3.

name: Slaying Giants - Week 2
description: We all know greed is a problem — we just think it’s a problem for other people. Greed is sneaky like that. Don't let greed grab a hold of you. Learn to see greed for what it is, slay its hold on your life, and stay free from greed for good.

name: Need To Know 10/10/2017
description: Jennifer Deweil tells us about our new series starting in KidSpring.

name: Slaying Giants - Week 1
description: When God’s people reached the Promised Land, it was full of abundance. It was also full of giants. The same is true for us. God has called us into abundance, but there are giants standing in our way. Don't allow these giants to steal one ounce of joy or hope from you. Know who they are and get ready to attack.

name: Fuse - Chosen Youth Week 2
description: Your role in life is to set an example and you were made to go first. "

name: Promised Land - Week 6
description: When we take communion, God calls us to examine our hearts so He can expand our faith. Are the promises of salvation, freedom, purpose, and family being fulfilled in your life? Learn how these four promises fit in the first communion celebration and hear how God is fulfilling these promises for ordinary people in our church.

name: Fuse - Chosen Youth Week 1
description: Jesus wants you to know who He is. Jesus wants you to know who you are. You were made for this. Will you work with Him?

name: Promised Land - Week 5
description: We long for real connection, to be part of something bigger than ourselves. God fulfills this desire by welcoming us into His family, the Church. God's family is no ordinary family. It is a place of unity and diversity. A place where you have nothing to prove and no one to impress. Learn what it means to be part of God’s family and why it’s like no other family you’ve ever known.

name: Promised Land - Week 4
description: God loves a good comeback story just as much as we do. Redemption appears throughout the Bible, and it's the story God wants to write for each of us. So what does redemption have to do with purpose? The reality is we'll never know what we were made to do until we know who we are. If we want to discover our purpose, we have to first understand the promise of redemption.

name: Promised Land - Week 3
description: Freedom is a process that begins at salvation. God continues to work out his promises in our lives to set us free and give us an abundant life. Watch this message to learn how Jesus is the key to a life of true freedom.

name: What is Tithing?
description: Tithing is to give back to God the first 10 cents on every dollar we earn, and we do that through giving to the local church. He asks us to give our tithe first, before we spend the rest, to show Him that He is first in our lives.\n

name: The Fight - Week 2

We're excellent at seeking, but we're lousy at finding true satisfaction. When all of our seeking leaves us empty, it's time to make a change. You were wired to seek. Now discover the one thing worth seeking.

description: There are lots of reasons we don’t pray. We worry about what to say, and we fear our requests will seem small compared to the problems of the world. Doesn’t God have better things to do? Why would He listen to us anyway? Often our reasons for not praying are signs we don’t fully understand what prayer is. Discover six things prayer is and why it’s important for every Christian — even you.

name: IF - Week 2
description: Pride is a human tendency. It shows up in all areas of our lives, and if left unaddressed, it can stop us from experiencing God’s best. Pride will shackle our lives, but humility is the key that will free our lives. Let these three reflections on humility help you break free from pride.

name: Easter at NewSpring
description: Condemned to death by the religious elite, Jesus was killed and placed in a tomb. But three days later, He walked out of the grave and the world was never the same. While most accounts of the Easter story stop there, Jesus’ journey did not.\n\nJesus left the tomb and joined two of his followers on a 7-mile walk from Jerusalem to Emmaus. Jesus met these men in their grief and disbelief, and showed them they were not alone, forgotten, or mistaken.

They were taking part in the Passover, a meal designed to help God’s people remember the four promises God made as they were leaving Egypt. Those promises are still true for each of us today. Discover how the communion we take today is a powerful reflection of the life God promises to each of us.

name: FUSE Grave Diggers - Week 2

name: One Person Can Make A Difference | Stories| Ben Duncan
description:
When God spoke to Ben Duncan about a move to NewSpring Charleston, all Ben knew was that he wanted to work with the local Fuse ministry to reach middle-school boys with the love of Jesus.

He expected, perhaps, to help a few boys with some homework - not unleash a wave of lifechange that transformed four families for eternity.

Watch the video to see how one person can make all the difference.

name: Change - Week 5
description: Did you know that sharing your story can lead to salvation? Watch today and see how a demon possessed man and a college student experienced the exponential impact of sharing their story.

name: FUSE Family Matters - Week 3
description: Everyone needs friends that will stick with you no matter what.

name: The Hunger Games - Trailer
description: Every battle begins with hunger. Whether it's wealth, power or freedom, we're all hungry for something.  And it's our hunger that drives us — it's the light that gets us through and the whole point of why we fight. Right now, you're in a battle — it could be a battle for your marriage, your children, your purity or your finances. Whatever it may be, you've got the hunger and now you're standing in the battle and faced with a choice: run or stand and fight? What are you hungry for? Are you willing to fight for it?

name: Change - Week 4
description: Life has given us #hashtags that are often difficult to overcome--#unattractive #accident #unloved #broken #stupid. There is only one person who has the right to #hashtag you. Listen today to learn who it is.

name: Out In The Wild: Arctic Chill Elementary Promo
Change - Week 3
description: God wants to bless you, but do you trust Him? This message will stretch your understanding of God's abundant provision for your life.

name: FUSE Family Matters - Week 2
description: We all need someone older than us, who loves Jesus, in our lives.

name: How to be Rich - 9 Rungs to a Fully Funded Life
description: Living a fully-funded life means you have the ability to do exactly what you’ve been put on earth to do, regardless of the cost. No matter where you currently are with your finances, you can live a fully-funded life! Joseph Sangl explains in this session the nine rungs of the ladder you can climb and ways that you can remain stable with your finances once you've reached the top rung.

name: Retirement Calculation
description: It’s a day that comes for all of us at one point in our lives. After years of work, we get tired and we all want to do one thing: retire. And when retirement comes, you leave behind one of two things: an inheritance for your children’s children or a legacy of debt. Are you on track to live and pass on a financially blessed life?

name: How To Get Paid When You're Not Working
description: There are only two possible outcomes for your finances: emptiness or abundance. The key to living abundantly with your finances is ensuring that you have enough oxen in your life to lead the way to financial freedom through hard work and inspired effort. Do you have oxen in your life? Are you taking care of the oxen you have?

name: Debt Elimination
description: No matter how big it is, you can be freed from your debt! Having debt freedom will transform how you view money and how you live your life. In this session, Joseph Sangl explains how to use a Debt Freedom Calculator and talks about the importance of setting a date to be free from your debt.

name: Budgeting
description: Are you scared of budgeting? Does a budget seem pointless to you? Think again! A budget is the engine of financial planning that will propel you toward your financial plans, hopes and dreams. In this session, Joseph Sangl tells you the importance of budgeting and gives tips on how to successfully plan your money so that you can anticipate God’s blessings in your finances.

name: Change Your Financial Future!
description: What do you need to change this year to bring your finances more in line with God’s work in your life? Is your financial preparation showing that you expect God to do big things in your life or are your stuck in a debt trap? In this session, Joseph Sangl teaches four core principles to empower you to find freedom in your finances and begin to win with money, God’s way.

name: Funding Your Plans, Hopes, and Dreams
description: Do you have a big dream that you’re scared to talk about because you’re sure someone will say you’re dumb for dreaming it? The great news is that God is in the miracle business and He wants you to have big dreams that will bring Him glory! But we have to start preparing financially, trusting that God wants to work miracles in our lives and make our big dreams happen. Do you know how much the big dream God has given you will cost? Are you financially ready it?

name: Compound Interest and Investing
description: Are your current investments matching the work of God? Are you living in the belief that Jesus is enough and God owns your finances? In this session, Joseph Sangl wraps up by talking about compound interest and how having it helps push us toward financial success.

God wants to do more than you can ask for or imagine with it. Learn how to have the abundant life Jesus promised when you turn your finances from worry into worship.

name: Step Up - Week 2
description: God doesn't want us to give because He wants something from us. God wants us to return what is already His because He wants something greater for us. Are you willing to give back to God what He's given you?

name: God is Faithful
description: Everyone wants to be successful. Everyone desires to be great in some way. But what do we need to do today to get to the destination we desire tomorrow?

description: The thief on the cross waited until his last minute to make Jesus Lord. Don’t wait till your last minute. Surrender to Christ now and walk through life with him!

name: Remember to Celebrate - Stand Alone
description: Thankfulness is the rear view mirror for a Christian. Glancing back and remembering how faithful God has been in the past spurs us to focus on the greater that He has prepared ahead.

name: FSKO 2013 - Night 3
description: The woman at the well felt marked by past mistakes, but Jesus loved her anyway. The Gospel is not about behaving, it’s about belonging.

name: FSKO 2013 - Night 1
description: The world categorizes people based on whether they are bad or good. However, we have all sinned, making us dead in God's eyes. Through his son Jesus we can be made new and alive.

name: I Heart My Church - Stand Alone
description: It's not uncommon to hear "I love football" or "I love ice cream" or "I love hunting", but when someone says "I love my church" people think it's weird. Watch this message to learn what the church is and why it matters.

name: Step Up Promo
description: God has never called His church to step back. He has always called us to step up!

description: Prayer is the one tool that every Christian has to empower their leaders. It’s the right tool for the job of encouraging those in leadership and pastoral ministry over us. So how do you use it?

name: FUSE Turn Up - Week 8
description: We have a hope in Jesus that's louder than any problem, stronger than any storm and constant through any trial. It's time to tap in to His power by turning up our praise.

name: Redneck - Week 2
description: The God of the universe stepped in to the world camouflaged as a man who came to serve. We must use our "camouflage" so that by all possible means some might be saved.

name: FUSE Turn Up - Week 7
description: Hundreds of students sent in questions about growing up and following Jesus. Join us as we turn up our summer and tackle the top questions with answers from the Bible.

name: FUSE Turn Up - Week 6
description: Jesus never commands anyone to act childish, but He does command us to be childlike. This week at Fuse we talk about turning our childish behavior into childlike faith for God's glory, the world's good and our joy.

name: Redneck - Week 1
description: When you're wild at heart, you're willing to do whatever it takes to get the job done. If you know Jesus, you have a life-changing message to share. Will you proclaim it boldly?

name: FUSE Turn Up - Week 5
description: When God made man, He knit a love of relationship into man's heart. Join us as we discuss how community strengthens and isolation endangers this week at Fuse!

name: FUSE Turn Up - Week 4
description: It is normal in our culture and world to "almost" make a difference. However, Jesus calls His followers to do extraordinary things and always trust in Him. This week at Fuse we discuss how to turn our almost into always.

name: FUSE Turn Up - Week 3
description: Jesus wants one thing for us: to know Him. When we invest in the discipline of walking with Jesus, He will develop our character to be more like Him.

name: FUSE Turn Up - Week 2
description: Has there ever been a time in your life when you felt closer to God than you do right now? How do you get back to that fellowship with God? Join us this week at Fuse as we look into the Bible and learn how to turn our relationship with God into fellowship with God.

name: FUSE Turn Up - Week 1
description: The early church wasn't scared to stand for Jesus because of what they had seen and heard. This week at Fuse we're talking about turning up for Jesus because we have seen too much to be quiet!

name: FUSE Level Up - Week 4
description: Moses built a bronze serpent staff that healed people who were bitten by snakes – Numbers 21:41. In the same way, we must get our lost friends to Jesus, who is the cure for their infection of sin.

name: FUSE Level Up - Week 3
description: By washing the disciples' feet, Jesus displayed humility, taught how to love others, and modeled how we receive cleansing. Jesus is not afraid of our mess, so we shouldn't be afraid to "clean" others with the gospel of Jesus.

name: FUSE Level Up - Week 2
description: Jesus was ruler of the universe and still modeled humility for us. We should follow his example and submit to those responsible for us, no matter what our family dynamic is.

name: FUSE Level Up - Week 1
description: Jesus is the King of Kings, the Lord of Lords. Yet, he was born in a manger covered in dirt in the most humble birth imaginable to show us that our lives are to be lived in pursuit of humility.

name: FUSE PMPK - Week 6
description: What happens after I die? Where will I go? What will I do? This week we are looking at what Jesus promises when it comes to our life after this one.

name: FUSE PMPK - Week 5
description: Jesus did not die on the cross for his people to stay defeated in a corner but to stand in freedom! We can hold fast to this promise that Jesus always provides an escape from temptation!

name: FUSE PMPK - Week 4
description: Jesus promises christians that he will never leave them or forsake them, and that He is with them throughout every season.

name: Grace - Week 2
description: The problem isn’t that we are bad; the problem is that we are dead. And, no amount of physical effort will bridge the distance from death to life. There is only one way to life and His name is Jesus.

name: Grace - Week 1

name: Chains - Week 3
description: Most of us trust God with some things, but not with everything. When we slow down and recognize who Jesus is, we'll learn to trust Him with everything.

name: Chains - Week 2
description: We doubt God's love because of past choices or present circumstances. In this message, you'll learn how God's promises and His character confirm His love for you.

name: Chains - Week 1
description: We've all felt trapped by circumstances, and often want to give up because our circumstances become chains that bind us. Don't quit. There is hope! True freedom begins when you focus on Jesus.

name: FUSE PMPK - Week 3

name: FUSE Spirit Week - Week 3

name: FUSE Spirit Week - Week 2
description: As humans, we mess up. We don't do everything perfectly all the time. However, there is hope. There is a Helper who graciously exposes our faults and lovingly purifies our hearts. Join us in week two of Spirit Week as we continue to learn about the Holy Spirit.

name: FUSE Spirit Week - Week 1
description: Who or what is the Holy Spirit? Why does the Holy Spirit matter in your life? This week we tackle these questions as we kick off our new series, Spirit Week.

name: FUSE 5 Words - Week 5
description: How many times have you wished for a better life? Have you ever wished for things like more money, less stress, a larger house, a smaller debt?

name: FUSE 5 Words - Week 4
description: All of us make decisions everyday based off of the word we are discussing in Fuse this week. You're invited to listen in on our fourth word: Believe.

name: FUSE 5 Words - Week 3
description: If God really is out there and sin really is in us then how do we "get clean" of it? Join us as we look to Jesus in the Bible and unfold this word that can impact us forever: Substitute.

name: FUSE 5 Words - Week 2

name: FUSE 5 Words - Week 1
description: Is there a God? Who is God? Is He real? Why does God matter to me? This week at Fuse we're talking about the reality of God, who He is and why it matters.

name: FUSE Once Upon A Time - Week 2

name: FUSE Once Upon A Time - Week 1

name: R.J. Jones

name: Joe Riding

description: In 2 Corinthians 5, we find that as Christians, we are compelled by the love of Jesus, but outside the walls of Christianity, we are controlled entirely by the power of sin.

However, what we can not change is what we offer, and that's the Word of God. The Bible must remain as the driving source of our daily life, and the highest authority in our personal walk. This week we're discussing the truth of the Bible and its effect on our lives.

description: There are two groups of people in the world: the righteous and the wicked. The righteous live a life blessed by God, and the wicked live under God’s curse. The natural state of every human is wickedness. Righteousness is found in Christ alone.

description: The chief end of man is to glorify God by enjoying Him forever. The thought this week is that we will be most effective at glorifying God if we are most satisfied in the life and purpose that He has for us.

description: John the Baptist understood that he was called to live his life for the glory of God. He knew he was called to become less and less so that Jesus could become greater and greater. That's the call on our lives--to take all of the glory off of ourselves and to give it all to Jesus.

description: Finishing well.

description: Glory matters because it’s what the entire universe is all about.

description: When it comes to taking the Land, our posture determines our portion.

In our lives, taking the land requires the same from us, only the obstacle in our path is the sin in our lives. We're called to be violent in killing our sin and killing our flesh.

description: Don't let worry, stress and anxiety control your life. Listen today and learn to overcome being overwhelmed by your circumstances.

description: When you stop trying to change the things around you and begin asking God to fix what is broken in you, your life will be transformed forever. As Pastor Perry shares honestly about some dark times in his own life, we'll see how only God can use pain for progress.

name: Overwhelmed - Week 1
description: When you focus on Jesus, you will understand that God is greater than your circumstances and He is able to pull you through.

name: All In - Week 1
description: A growing relationship with Jesus is intentional, not accidental. What does it mean to intentionally love Jesus with all my heart?

description: If you want your life to be blessed, you must learn to submit and surrender to the voice of Christ.

name: The Life Of Job - Week 3

name: The Life Of Job - Week 1

name: NewSpring Welcomes - Week 3
description: Whether we realize it or not, each of us was created for a great cause. We will never be truly fulfilled until we find and pursue it.

name: NewSpring Welcomes - Week 2

description: Baptism is a priority, a proclamation, it happens in a progression and is not private. Is this your next step?

description: Today we'll examine God's original design for sex and why He provided it.

name: Revelation - Week 2
description: What we value will ultimately determine what we do.

name: Revelation - Week 1
description: Jesus is alive and present in the Church. He reigns in authority with passion. He is faithful, knows all things and is the only way to be saved.

description: Sara Schenck thought she had tried everything to overcome the emptiness she felt from a life filled with tragedy …

description: What kinds of fruit are you bearing? The bible says that a bad tree will bear bad fruit and a good tree will produce good fruit. “A man ought to examine himself” to see what kind of fruit is being produced.

description: As you examine the most recognized verse in all of scripture phrase by phrase, realize the profound love God demonstrated toward you when He gave His Son for your forgiveness and salvation.

description: Believing and receiving the good news of Jesus Christ means an abundant life now and an eternity spent in heaven. The consequences of not accepting the finished work of Jesus is an eternity spent separated from Jesus in hell.

description: Why do religious people tend to sometimes miss what Jesus is doing around them?

name: The Gospel - Week 4
description: Jesus concludes The Sermon on the Mount with a warning to apply his teaching.

name: Now What? - Week 3
description: What must you do in order to move from where you are to where you need to be?

name: Now What? - Week 2
description: Through Jesus Christ, we have been given complete access to God. God wants to have a continuing relationship with us. That’s why prayer is such an important part of the Christian experience. Through prayer and bible study we can maintain a power connection to our Father.

name: Now What? - Week 1
description: So often we rank our requests with a degree of difficultly. Thinking that God would be bothered with the “small” stuff, we keep those requests to ourselves and become overwhelmed with worry.

name: In Rhythm - Week 4
description: It's time for us as a church to get back to who God is calling us to be and what He is calling us to do. It's time to get comfortable with the uncomfortable and let go of any conditions that keep us from following God. If we want to be the church God wants us to be we've got to…

name: In Rhythm - Week 6
description: God has not called you to slip into the world, unnoticed. He wants you to bravely stand out in the world around you, sharing the truth of Jesus!

name: In Rhythm - Week 3
description: You are way too valuable to sit on the sidelines! God has called you to be something specific and it starts when you follow what He's called you to do.

name: In Rhythm - Week 5
description: Jesus is still changing lives, one life at a time! In this message we took a step back to hear three stories of people that have experienced life change and hope through Jesus.\n

name: In Rhythm - Week 1
description: Sometimes a simple conversation can prevent a tragic devastation. Is there a real conversation you know you need to have but aren't having?

name: In Rhythm - Week 2
description: Is it ok to be mad at the church? Is it the church that hurts or its people? In this message Perry addresses three reasons that people get mad and what happens when we let anger reign in our lives.\n\n

name: How To Survive The End Of The World - Week 2
description: The Bible teaches that we will all face judgment. At The Judgment Seat of Christ, Christ-followers will be held accountable for their stewardship of the gifts, resources and time that have been given to them by God.

name: How To Survive The End Of The World - Week 5
description: This is the truth that all of us must face: after our death it will be too late to deal with Jesus. Today is the day of Salvation!

name: How To Survive The End Of The World - Week 1
description: Many have attempted to set a date for the Lord’s return despite His warning that date-setting is a waste of precious time. Instead of looking for hidden clues and codes we should see the obvious signs all around us and begin our preparations now.

name: How To Survive The End Of The World - Week 3
description: In Revelation, we no longer see Him as a suffering servant but as returning King, Victor over death and hell, King of kings and Lord of lords.

name: How To Survive The End Of The World - Week 4
description: The great mystery of what happens when we die is answered in God’s Word. As Christ-followers we can face death without fear.

name: Home for Christmas - Week 3
description: Do you want to go through life scared or do you want to go through life with eager anticipation of the great and mighty things that God wants to do through you?

name: Home for Christmas - Week 4
description: “Home” brings out two contrasting feelings within most people. People want to stray from home or go on vacations, but while away, they long for the comfort and refuge of the very place from which they longed to escape.

name: Home for Christmas - Week 2
description: Have you ever taken any time to think about how mighty God is?

name: Home for Christmas - Week 1
description: Throughout scripture we learn that we are able to be confident in the fact that God will speak to us. God speaks to us in a variety of ways: At times we may actually hear His voice, at times we hear His voice through the words of scripture, and at times He speaks through those around us. We all too often desire to hear from God but are not in tune enough with Him to know how or when He is speaking

name: God Is... - Week 3
description: When we accept Jesus, we are spiritually born into God’s family. What a joy to know that God is our heavenly Father and he wants good things for His children.

name: God is... - Week 5
description: In times of extraordinary uncertainty, when it seems that God is most distant, we can be sure that he is doing his best work.

name: God Is... - Week 4
description: What an amazing assurance to know that God is with you at all times.

name: God Is... - Week 2
description: Not only does God love us, God is love. It is the reflection of the essence of who He is.

name: God Is... - Week 1
description: We can be intimately acquainted with the greatness and goodness of God through a personal relationship with Jesus Christ because “God was pleased to have all his fullness dwell in him”

name: Don't Get Married Until... - Week 5
description: Today, we talk about dealing with our junk and why doing that sets us up for success in marriage.

name: Don't Get Married Until... - Week 3
description: This week we focus on the characteristics of a woman a godly man should pursue.

name: Don't Get Married Until... - Week 4
description: When we fail to build those accountability measures into our dating and marriage we set ourselves up for stagnation, poor choices, and heartbreak.

name: Don't Get Married Until... - Week 2
description: It is vital that men and women understand biblical manhood and spiritual leadership so that we set ourselves up for success in our potential or current marriage.

name: Don't Get Married Until... - Week 1
description: Many will impatiently rush toward marriage assuming all is lost if single past the age of 22 and once married, talk about marriage as if it were medieval torture.

name: Five Lies of the Devil - Week 1
description: The Bible says in John 8:44 that the devil is a liar and the father of lies. In this session we delve into scripture to combat one of the common lies that the devil uses to lead us into fear and worry.

name: Five Lies of the Devil - Week 5
description: God designed sex. When sex happens outside of God’s plan, sex is destructive. Satan wants to destroy us and he’ll use sex to do it.

name: Five Lies of the Devil - Week 2
description: It’s easy to say up front that we want to follow Christ in every area of our life, but when it comes to money, are we serious?

name: Five Lies of the Devil - Week 4
description: In our pluralistic society we sometimes are very careful not to make a public stand for our beliefs in fear that we might be viewed as narrow or dogmatic.

name: Five Lies of the Devil - Week 3
description: We make hundreds of decisions each day, most of which are fairly insignificant. But sometimes lifechanging decisions with far-reaching consequences have to be made. To make a God-honoring decision we must rely on more than our senses or feelings or experiences.

name: On The Farm - Week 4
description: Why aren't my kids allowed into the service? Why can't I re-enter the service after I leave? Money? Answers to some frequently asked questions about NewSpring Church.\n

name: On The Farm - Week 3
description: In the Bible there is only one perfect father and He is God. He is visible, audible, holy and compassionate.

name: On the Farm - Week 2
description: In this two-part message about the vision guiding NewSpring Church, Senior Pastor Perry Noble shares 10 things he wants for every NewSpring owner.

name: On the Farm - Week 1
description: In this two-part message about the vision guiding NewSpring Church, Senior Pastor Perry Noble shares 10 things he wants for every NewSpring owner.

name: More - Week 6
description: When storms happen and you cry out to Jesus sometimes He is silent. Where is He? Does He care? Learn answers to these questions and more in today's message.

name: The Best Is Yet To Come - Week 3
description: Faithfulness. It is a word that describes the first ten years of Newspring Church. Newspring Church has prayed and asked God to show up and change lives and He has been faithful to do just that.

name: More - Week 5
description: Does your giving show faith or are you giving from the leftovers? As you return the first and the best the rest is blessed.

name: More - Week 4
description: When you return God's portion to His house, the remainder is blessed. Learn to live the blessed life by returning the tithe and giving generously.

name: More - Week 3
description: Mothers have a high calling that is often overwhelming. Today's message will encourage, challenge and remind you that all things are possible with God.

name: More - Week 2
description: Many people experience fellowship with Jesus, but do not have a relationship with Him. Jesus directs us to God's opportunities and enables us to see clearly what He wants us to do.

name: Melissa Wilson
description: Melissa Wilson had an abortion on the day of her 16th birthday. Her shame, guilt and grief, felt like a curse overshadowing her life, until she talked to a friend who invited her to NewSpring …

name: Brian Elmore
description: Brian Elmore had no desire for a relationship with Jesus until his brother's death caused him to rethink everything he ever knew.

name: More - Week 1
description: Jesus came to provide hope and a future that transcends the temporal satisfaction of stuff.

name: NewSpring Church - Week 6
description: The reality is that any of us could give in to temptation & have an affair. Learn how to avoid the pitfalls and keep your vows to God and your wife.

name: NewSpring Church - Week 5
description: Men, learn to be more like Jesus and lead your marriage the way God intended.

name: NewSpring Church - Week 4
description: When is the right time to get married? When you’re both in love with Jesus and obedient to scripture.

name: NewSpring Church - Week 3
description: Explore two common myths about sex that lead to confusion and a cheapening of God’s creation.

name: NewSpring Church - Week 2
description: God lays out basic principles in scripture for women that will change the way you act towards others. Hear the truth that God loves and treasures you, and be set free to transform your marriage by being a godly wife.

name: NewSpring Church - Week 1
description: If Jesus isn’t first in your finances, your money problems become marriage problems. Learn how to partner with your spouse to manage money with a biblical perspective.

name: Identity Theft - Week 2
description: Jesus wants His church to be a solution to the broken world ahead of us. In this message, Christine Caine shares stories from her life as she presses the importance of our role in the church—to bring life to a broken world.\n

name: Identity Theft - Week 3
description: You have been plucked out of eternity and positioned exactly where you are to fulfill a specific purpose. Will you accept it?\n\n

name: Identity Theft - Week 1
description: Do you ever feel like you're living an average life that is settled and meaningless at best? God wants to do great and meaningful things that are greater than you could ever imagine in and through your life. The question is, are you willing to let Him?\n\n

name: Identity Theft - Week 4
description: There is one thing that we all underestimate on a regular basis: Ourselves! God has gifted each and everyone of us and He wants to use our gifts to build up His church. Are you living the life God called you to live using the gifts He's given you?

description: In anticipation of the Easter 2011 services, NewSpring Church gathered for a night of worship & prayer.

description: When you meet Jesus and learn what's important to Him, you'll make adjustments that can set you free from greed.

description: God wants to do more in and through your life than you could ever imagine and it all starts with the willingness to say, “I surrender everything.”\n\n

name: Make War - Week 2
description: The snapshot of your past is not the definition of your life. In order to get past your past, you've got to stop letting it define you and start letting God's forgiveness, choosing, value and love define you.\n\n

description: What do cancer, a tragic car wreck, a widow and a widower have in common? Find out today as we experience real stories of triumph through tragedy.

description: You won't forgive. You can't move on. Forgiveness is a choice that enables you to live in complete freedom. Upgrade today by choosing to forgive.

name: Megan Davis
description: Raped as a teenager, Megan Davis was trapped in the anger and pain of losing her innocence.

name: Make War - Week 7
description: The now is preparation for the next. And, God won't give you what's next until you're faithful with what's now.

name: Make War - Week 6
description: Are you stuck or facing opposition? You are only one decision away from breakthrough.

name: Make War - Week 5
description: What do cancer, a tragic car wreck, a widow and a widower have in common? Find out today as we experience real stories of triumph through tragedy.

name: Erik Fitzgerald and Matthew Swatzell
description: After a deadly car wreck, Erik Fitzgerald and Matthew Swatzell crossed paths in a way that would change them forever.

name: Mandy Smith
description: At 32, Mandy Smith lost Zac, her husband and best friend of 17 years, to a year-long battle with cancer, leaving her to care for her three children. She doesn't know why God would allow this tragedy to happen, but she is choosing to praise God, knowing his goodness.

name: Make War - Week 4
description: We may never know why tragedy happens, but when we understand who God is, tragedy becomes triumph.

name: Make War - Week 3
description: When you understand that God wants to do more in and through you than you could ever imagine, you won't settle for anything less.

name: Make War - Week 2
description: The haunting of a troubled past is overcome by understanding your identity in Jesus.

description: Gauntlet 2011 Promo

name: Make War - Week 1
description: When it comes to following Jesus there are only two options: for Him or against Him. Where do you stand?

name: Hope - Week 4
description: Jesus is not just ordinary but rather is extraordinary. When we perceive this we will receive Him for who He really is.

name: Hope - Christmas Eve 2010 - Week 4
description: Jesus is not just ordinary but rather is extraordinary. When we perceive this we will receive Him for who He really is.

name: Hope - Week 3
description: Can there be peace in a tumultuous world that maintains the appearance of stability but seldom obtains it? Today's message will help you understand what peace is and how to have true peace in your life.

name: Hope - Week 3 ALL
description: Can there be peace in a tumultuous world that maintains the appearance of stability but seldom obtains it? Today's message will help you understand what peace is and how to have true peace in your life.

name: Hope - Week 2
description: Am I a follower of Christ, or am I merely fond of Him? It is important to examine the unexamined areas of your life to reveal the true answer.

name: Hope - Week 2 ALL
description: Am I a follower of Christ, or am I merely fond of Him? It is important to examine the unexamined areas of your life to reveal the true answer.

name: Hope - Week 1
description: Do you feel trapped without hope of rescue? Through the story of the rescued Chilean miners, we learn an important lesson about our own rescue.

name: Man vs Wife - 11:15
description: Senior Pastor Perry Noble and his wife Lucretia answer questions about marriage, sex, dating and relationships that were texted in during the service.\n

name: Man vs Wife - Week 6
description: Our God-given appetites are never fully and finally satisfied. Are you trading what matters more for that which might fulfill you in the short run?

name: Man vs Wife - Week 5
description: How to stop being a victim and start living in the victory that only Jesus can provide.

name: Man vs Wife - Week 4
description: Learn how relationships are maximized when we are willing to get on the same page.

name: Jason and Jennifer Hall
description: Jennifer and Jason Hall got married hastily and literally ended up hating one another. But what was irretrievably broken, was just the beginning of something new…

name: Man vs Wife - Week 3
description: In relationships you have two options; stay or walk away. Listen to find out which option is right for you.

name: Hillary Bolt
description: Food was the only way Hillary Bolt knew how to control her emotions until Jesus taught her about his strength in her weakness.

name: Kristy Carver
description: Kristy Carver was content to be a passive attender at NewSpring for three years before she began to serve, and that's when her relationship with Jesus truly began ...

name: Chip Schneider
description: Chip Schneider didn't teach his children to know Jesus. They taught him.

name: David Bradshaw
description: David Bradshaw hated God for taking the wife he cherished. Until Jesus replaced anger with peace.

name: Jay Davis
description: Jay Davis thought his life was as good as it could get. But he soon discovered that Jesus wasn't interested in his comfort, only his joy.

name: Laura White
description: Laura White once believed that there was nothing beyond life on earth. But it was her love of animals that led her to the truth.

name: Ryan Mahaffey
description: Ryan Mahaffey had pushed away Jesus, his wife and his family. But he couldn't resist God's grace.

name: Mark and Shawna Asbell
description: Mark and Shawna Asbell faced a mountain of debt and a looming bankruptcy, and it was just what their marriage needed ...

name: Robin Atkins
description: God gave Robin Atkins freedom from domestic violence, drug abuse, and homelessness, but she had to trust God with her money before she grasped how good Jesus really was …

name: Michael and Cindy Atkins
description: Michael and Cindy Atkins discovered what happens when a group of Christians showed them the grace that covers a multitude of sins

name: Man vs Wife - Week 2
description: In this challenge to men, we'll look at biblical manhood and learn to approach marriage with a "No Matter What!" commitment.

name: Man vs Wife - Week 1
description: Your marriage (or future marriage) will go beyond your imagination when you focus on your responsibilities rather than your rights!

name: Sun Stand Still - Week 2
description: What is the Gospel and why is it central to following Jesus?

name: Sun Stand Still - Week 1
description: What happens when you dare to ask God for the impossible? Dreams are realized. Lives are transformed. The world is changed. And the impossible happens.

name: The Blessed Life - Week 3
description: When you have a plan, follow that plan and prepare for the unexpected events of life, you are setting yourself up for financial success.

name: Nick Pratt
description: Emergency room worker Nick Pratt didn't understand life until he understood the meaning of the death of one 3-year-old girl.

name: Jamie Beasley
description: Jamie Beasley prayed for healing for his damaged foot for three long years — he just never believed that it would happen.

name: The Blessed Life - Week 2
description: If we want more blessings from God, we have to be trustworthy with the money and stuff we already have; we have to use them as Jesus commands.

name: The Blessed Life - Week 1
description: If Jesus isn't first in your finances He can't be Lord of your life. In this message, we'll examine three things you cannot do if you want to be blessed.

name: Will Ervin
description: Will Ervin thought Jesus was a fairytale and church was all about the rules. Until his addictions forced him to reach out for hope...

name: I Love the 80's - Week 5
description: Following Jesus leads to growth, and growing people change. Today's message provides practical steps you can take to facilitate growth in your own life.

name: Brooke George
description: Brooke George thought the love and faith of her All-American family was all the security she needed until God took it all away.

name: Emmett Kerr
description: Emmett Kerr's life looked as normal as every other teenager's in Florence, South Carolina. But he was holding onto a dark secret and he knew it would come to light.

name: I Love the 80's - Week 4
description: When found people find people and saved people serve it prepares the way for people to meet Jesus. Listen to find out if you know Jesus and how you can be certain of your relationship with Him.

name: I Love the 80's - Week 3
description: In scripture, anytime someone walked away from the people of God, they always walked away from God. Find out why community is essential to your commitment to follow Christ.

name: Lisa Fisher
description: At the age of 24, Lisa Fisher faced the possibility she would never see, walk or talk again. But God wanted more than her physical healing.

name: Evangelism Seminar
description: We're called to "go and make disciples of all nations." But most of us don't. Why is that? Why do we gloss over or ignore one of the basic tenants of Christianity?\n\nWhat are the realities of evangelism that we must deal with? What can we learn from Jesus about evangelism? What are practical things we can do to prepare to share our faith with others? Set aside two hours to engage with this simple, straightforward evangelism seminar taught by Senior Pastor Perry Noble. You don't have to fear sharing your faith anymore!

name: I Love the 80's - Week 2
description: According to the scriptures, saved people serve people. In order to serve effectively, we must see as Jesus sees and respond as Jesus leads.\n

name: I Love the 80's - Week 1
description: When you discover something that changes your life, you naturally want to share it with others. NewSpring church values evangelism. Find out what it is and how you can participate.

name: Fuse Landing Video
description: The intro video for the Fuse landing page. (newspring.cc/fuse)

name: I Heart My Church - Week 1
description: In order to have a church we love, we must understand the problem, the people and the potential. Only then will we assume responsibility and take ownership of God's church.

name: I Heart My Church - Week 1 ALL
description: In order to have a church we love, we must understand the problem, the people and the potential. Only then will we assume responsibility and take ownership of God's church.

description: Q&A from the 9:15am service. During each service, people were invited to text in questions which Perry answered.

description: Q&A from the 6:00pm service. During each service, people were invited to text in questions which Perry answered.

name: You Asked For It Live - Q&A - 11:15am
description: Q&A from the 11:15am service. During each service, people were invited to text in questions which Perry answered.

name: Lee Schnieder
description: Lee Schneider declared himself an atheist as a teenager. He was angry at the happiness of people around him. He wanted to be different. For years, his life centered around partying. He didn't know he had to be saved from himself…

name: Jad Dean
description: Jad Dean knew God had blessed him with a sweet foot. He was living the dream playing as a kicker for the Clemson University Tigers, well on his way to being a National Football League draft pick. But in his greatest on-field disappointment, he saw how GOd had only become his way to get what he wanted…

name: Bill Nickas
description: For Bill Nickas, an Anderson restauranteur, hard-partying meant more than his business, his marriage, and his health. But one of his loyal customers never stopped praying and inviting him to find the true meaning to life.

name: Mike Hunt
description: God used a fatal plane crash to teach Mike Hunt that Jesus Christ is the conqueror over death. It would be a lesson in belief that wasn't meant only for him. “If my suffering means people receive Chris, this will all be worth it.”

name: Nate Smith
description: In a near-fatal wreck Nate's survival was only the first miracle.\n\nA student's ordinary life came to a crashing halt with a tractor trailer during a family vacation. What happened next changed his rescue workers, his friends, and his family forever…

name: Kacie McCoy
description: Kacie McCoy had prayed the prayer. She thought she knew God. But she led a double life until someone reached out to help her.

name: Matt Beasley
description: When Jesus got hold of Matt Beasley, he knew instantly he had to do something to help the children around him who had no hope. It started with driving a few teenagers to NewSpring each week. Then God answered his big prayer in a way only God could…

name: Family Vacation - Week 5 ALL
description: Each week in KidSpring children meet Jesus on their level as they experience safe, age-appropriate environments where the Bible is taught in a creative and relevant way. Today KidSpring takes over the adult service so we can worship the way they do each week.

name: Family Vacation - Week 5
description: Each week in KidSpring children meet Jesus on their level as they experience safe, age-appropriate environments where the Bible is taught in a creative and relevant way. Today KidSpring takes over the adult service so we can worship the way they do each week.

name: Family Vacation - Week 4
description: We're called to fight for our family, and most days it feels like we're playing ";King of the Hill". We'll examine how our words and actions impact how successful we are at leading our family.

name: Family Vacation - Week 3
description: God is desperate for your joy, and His plan for enriching your life doesn't always line up with the plan you've made.

name: Identity Theft - Week 4
description: Are you living the life God called you to live using the gifts He's provided? In this message you'll learn about Ehud the Benjamite, an overweight king and how to leverage your uniqueness to make a difference.

name: Identity Theft - Week 3
description: You have been plucked out of eternity and positioned in time to fulfill a specific purpose. Guest speaker Christine Caine shares a bit of her life story as she challenges us to meet the needs we see around us.

name: Identity Theft - Week 2
description: Christine Caine, Global Ambassador for Hillsong Church shares stories from her life about a relationship that can rescue you from the destruction of a careless past and give you purpose in the midst of helplessness.

name: Identity Theft - Week 1
description: You were created for a purpose that far exceeds the marginal existence of a Chia Pet. By examining the life of the prophet Isaiah, we'll see how God makes himself known and learn to experience true freedom through total surrender.

name: Family Vacation - Week 2
description: Rock or Sand? What is your house built on? Today we'll examine five foundations that matter and learn how to build your family on the Rock.

name: Family Vacation - Week 1
description: It's summer time, but that's no reason to take a vacation from your family. Next time you're with them, be patient and self-controlled, give praise and encouragement, extend forgiveness, practice submission, offer instruction, pay attention.

name: Esther - Week 3
description: In this message, we'll read through the last three chapters of Esther as we continue to examine how a woman used her circumstances to save an entire race of people.

name: Esther - Week 2
description: Are you stuck in your walk with God? When you're driving around a "Christian cul-de-sac" doing all the right things but going nowhere, it's time to take your next step?

name: Esther - Week 1
description: Church is not a spectator sport where you can show up, be entertained and leave unchanged. If this describes your church experience, maybe you don't know Jesus. If you do know Jesus, then what are you waiting for? Get in the game.

name: Punctuation - Week 6
description: Are we going to be a Church that throws rocks at sinners? Or are we going to show grace? What if we lovingly invite the lost to go and sin no more?

name: Punctuation - Week 5
description: You appear to have it all together and know all the right words to say, but something is missing. In today's message, we'll read a story about a rich young ruler and ask the question, "What Do I Lack?"

name: Punctuation - Week 5
description: You appear to have it all together and know all the right words to say, but something is missing. In today's message, we'll read a story about a rich young ruler and ask the question, "What Do I Lack?"

name: Neicy Abrilz
description: All Neicy wanted was love. But deep down, from her earliest memory, she had always known she was on her own. Every one of her choices multiplied her pain and her shame—until her path took an unexpected turn.

name: Sarra Neshan
description: Sarra Neshan was a rebellious teenager who couldn't wait to leave home, and the stifling authority of her mother. At 17, she moved in with her boyfriend. She had two children with him. But the freedom she pursued felt more like a trap with every passing day. Until someone she never expected invited her to NewSpring…

name: Punctation - Week 4
description: In this message, Clayton King teaches about the authority of scripture, how we got the bible, why it matters and what we should do with the scripture that God has given us.

name: Eric & Lisa Drudge
description: Eric & Lisa Drudge did everything they could to destroy their marriage. And when they divorced, all they felt was relief. But that was just the beginning of their story…

name: Punctuation - Week 3
description: You didn't choose to be this far away, but over time, the decisions you made contributed to your drift off course. Don't give up. It's never to late to come back.

name: Ben Thomas
description: It was just a typical day on the campus of Auburn University, and Ben Thomas should have been paying more attention as he drove up to the railroad crossing. Lucky for him, somebody had his back…

name: Punctuation - Week 1
description: Jesus paid an unbelievable price to send an undeniable message. In today's message we'll examine the facts about Jesus and learn how far God went to show you how much He loves you.

name: Punctuation - Week 2
description: Do you know? How can I know for sure? Knowing Jesus is not a complicated mystery. It's as simple as meeting Him and knowing that your life is changed forever.

name: Practical Atheist - Week 5
description: Have you ever met a famous person? a movie star? professional athlete? rock star? How easy was it to share the story of that experience with someone? If you know Jesus, sharing your faith is as easy as telling people about someone you love.

name: Aimee Rogers and Sarah Chapman
description: Aimee Rodgers saw her younger sister, Sarah, fall into a pit of drug and alcohol addiction. She never lost hope that God would rescue Sarah, and she did the only thing she knew to do...

name: Practical Atheist - Week 4
description: In this podcast you'll hear stories of real people who met Jesus as the result of a simple invitation. What will you do to share the gospel? Who will you invite to church?

name: Practical Atheist - Week 3
description: Your actions reveal your beliefs, and what you believe influences your behavior. Through your daily interactions, do people see an actual Christian or a practical atheist? Student Pastor, Brad Cooper challenges us to consider our actions as we examine our beliefs.

name: Practical Atheist - Week 2
description: Do you have money or does money have you? Bills are piling up and the kids need food. Maybe you've heard that God provides, but you're not sure how that practically plays out. Listen to this message to hear what the Bible says about money and find out what your wallet says about you.

name: Practical Atheist - Week 1
description: Actual Christian or Practical Atheist? Why do we claim Jesus but deny Him in our daily actions? In this message we'll look at a remarkable story of answered prayer from the bible as we're challenged to overcome our superstitions and believe in the supernatural power of Jesus.

name: Zac Smith
description: At 32, Zac Smith wasn't expecting the diagnosis of stage 4 cancer. The disease brutalized his body day by day, but his faith in Christ only grew stronger. So much so, he wants to tell you why he is thankful for his cancer.
